Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Once the pan is hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%mins}. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and add them to the bowl with the corn. Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%can} in a sieve. Pop half the beans into another #bowl{} and mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Pop the (now empty) pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and @chorizo{90%g}. Stir-fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Stir in the garlic, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you don't like too much heat) and @tomato puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%min}, then stir in the @water{2%tbsp} for the sauce, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and mixed beans (whole and crushed).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Bring the filling to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%mins}. Meanwhile, grate both types of cheese.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g} and @red leicester cheese{60%g}. Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Add the lettuce to the bowl with the corn and tomatoes.

Once the chicken filling has thickened, remove the pan from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Lay the @super soft tortillas{4}(with whole wheat) on a #board{}, spoon the filling down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling. Drizzle a little @oil{} over the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{}, then lay in the wraps. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so they don't unroll. Top with the grated cheeses. Bake your enchiladas on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{10-12%mins}.

Meanwhile, drizzle a little @oil{} over the charred corn salad. Squeeze in some lime juice, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together. In a #small bowl{}, combine the @creme fraiche{75%g} and lime zest. Cut any remaining lime into wedges. When the enchiladas are ready, divide them between your plates (2 per person) and serve with the charred corn salad and a dollop of zesty creme fraiche. Serve the lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!